HB 1131 Original 2026 Regular Session Marcelle
Abstract: Provides that a registered voter shall not be moved to the inactive list of voters
until 30 days after an address confirmation notice is sent to the voter; eliminates the
annual canvass of voters conducted by the Dept. of State; requires that voter list
maintenance be conducted in a uniform, nondiscriminatory manner; requires the
secretary of state to publish quarterly reports of voter registration totals; limits the
secretary's ability to transfer voter registration data to a federal agency; requires the
